    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Asiatic wild ass. Among other characteristics, it may be distinguished by the color, which is lighter than the African ass, ranging from reddish to yellow-gray. The term "kulan" is sometimes used to refer to this species, although it is often reserved for the race, Equus hemionus hemionus.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
